---
title: "Messages"
description: "Send, react to, edit, and list iMessages"
---

import { TypeTooltip } from "/snippets/type-tooltip.mdx";

`im.messages` covers everything related to individual messages - sending plain text, rich multipart messages, reacting, editing, unsending, paginated listing, and real-time event subscriptions.

## Sending Messages

The SDK has three sending APIs. Use the simplest one that covers your use case.

<Tabs>
  <Tab title="Plain text">
    ```ts
    await im.messages.sendText(chat, "Hello!");
    ```
  </Tab>
  <Tab title="With options">
    ```ts
    import { MessageEffect } from "@photon-ai/advanced-imessage";

    await im.messages.sendText(chat, "Hello!", {
      effect: MessageEffect.confetti,
      replyTo: someMessageGuid,
      subject: "Hey",
    });
    ```

    {% set sendOpts = symbol("ts:@photon-ai/advanced-imessage#SendOptions") %}

    <Accordion title="SendOptions" description="{{ sendOpts.doc.summary }}">
      | Option | Type | Description |
      |---|---|---|
      {% for m in sendOpts.members -%}
      | `{{ m.name }}` | `{{ m.type.text | replace("\n", " ") | replace("    ", "") | replace("|", "\\|") | replace("<", "&lt;") | replace(">", "&gt;") }}` | {{ m.doc.summary }} |
      {% endfor %}
    </Accordion>
  </Tab>
  <Tab title="Multipart">
    Use `sendMultipart()` when you want per-part formatting or mentions.

    ```ts
    await im.messages.sendMultipart(chat, [
      { text: "Hey " },
      { mentionedAddress: "alice@icloud.com", text: "@Alice" },
      { text: "!" },
    ]);
    ```

    Formatting is specified per-part via `MessagePart.formatting` rather than at the top level; every other `SendOptions` field applies normally.
  </Tab>
</Tabs>

{% set messageType = symbol("ts:@photon-ai/advanced-imessage#Message") %}
All sending APIs return a <TypeTooltip name="Message" type={`{{ messageType.signature }}`} />.

### Send an attachment

Upload first, then send by GUID:

```ts
await im.messages.sendAttachment(chat, attachmentGuid);
```

