</Accordion>

## Catch up after disconnect

`im.events.catchUp()` replays durable events newer than a sequence cursor. Use it on reconnect to replay anything missed before resuming the live stream.

```ts
for await (const event of im.events.catchUp(42)) {
  if (event.type === "catchup.complete") {
    console.log("caught up to sequence", event.headSequence);
    break;
  }
}
```

## Real-time events

`subscribeEvents()` returns a `TypedEventStream<MessageEvent>`. Filter on `event.type` to handle specific event kinds.

```ts
for await (const event of im.messages.subscribeEvents()) {
  if (event.type === "message.received") {
    console.log(event.message.content.text);
    console.log(event.chatGuid);
  }
}
```

{% set messageEvent = symbol("ts:@photon-ai/advanced-imessage#MessageEvent") %}
<Accordion title="Message event types" description="{{ messageEvent.doc.summary }}">
  | `event.{{ messageEvent.discriminator }}` | Extra fields |
  |---|---|
  {% for v in messageEvent.variants -%}
  | `{{ v.name }}` | {% if v.fields and v.fields|length %}{% for f in v.fields %}`{{ f.name }}{% if f.optional %}?{% endif %}`{% if not loop.last %}, {% endif %}{% endfor %}{% else %}-{% endif %} |
  {% endfor %}
</Accordion>

### Stream operators

`TypedEventStream` supports `.filter()`, `.map()`, and `.take()`:

```ts
const incoming = im.messages
  .subscribeEvents()
  .filter(
    (e): e is Extract<MessageEvent, { type: "message.received" }> => e.type === "message.received",
  )
  .map((e) => ({
    from: e.message.sender?.address,
    text: e.message.content.text,
  }));

for await (const { from, text } of incoming) {
  console.log(`[${from}] ${text}`);
}
```

Streams implement `Symbol.asyncDispose`:

```ts
await using stream = im.messages.subscribeEvents();
for await (const event of stream) {
  if (event.type === "message.received") {
    console.log(event.message.content.text);
  }
}
```

## Miscellaneous

```ts
await im.messages.notifySilenced(chat, messageGuid);

const media = await im.messages.getEmbeddedMedia(chat, messageGuid);
```
